1
00:00:14,133 --> 00:00:15,900
<i>Why don't we ask
for ransom already?</i>

2
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,367
<i>I'm not doing this
for the money.</i>

3
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>We are.
So let's ask for ransom now.</i>

4
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,500
<i>Felma and I have
a strong feeling about this.</i>

5
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:25,833
<i>Hazel is definitely involved
in what happened to our kids.</i>

6
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> Where did she go?</i>

7
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,367
<i> Are you looking for me?</i>

8
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,567
<i> Are you stalking me?</i>

9
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:32,100
<i>Next time,
don't act so recklessly.</i>

10
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:37,267
<i>We just want to help get
justice for our family.</i>

11
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:38,833
<i>Alright, bro,
fix the blindfold.</i>

12
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:41,133
<i> You traitor! You animal!</i>

13
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,500
<i> Jeffrey! Wait!</i>

14
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,133
<i> I won't hurt you.</i>

15
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> Listen to me!</i>

16
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,833
<i> I'm getting you out of here!</i>

17
00:00:49,967 --> 00:00:51,000
<i> Where's Jeffrey?</i>

18
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:52,333
<i>What is this?
He escaped from you?</i>

19
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:53,567
<i> It was Jojo!</i>

20
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:56,633
<i>You're a bastard, Jojo! Traitor!</i>

21
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:57,833
<i> Are they on the same side now?</i>

22
00:00:57,967 --> 00:00:58,933
<i> Bro, thanks.</i>

23
00:00:59,067 --> 00:01:00,400
<i>I'm just trying to rectify
my past mistakes.</i>

24
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:02,167
<i> He's gonna tell Felma!</i>

25
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:03,867
<i> Jeffrey, my son.</i>

26
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,867
<i> What happened to you?</i>

27
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:07,867
<i> It was Hazel.</i>

28
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,900
<i> Hazel did this to you?</i>

29
00:01:12,767 --> 00:01:13,800
Yeah, it was Hazel.

30
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:18,833
She's the demon
who had me kidnapped, Mom.

31
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,267
I knew it.

32
00:01:21,967 --> 00:01:24,467
That woman is pure evil.

33
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:27,733
Her soul's already burning
in hell.

34
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:30,200
Rotting. Decaying.

35
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:33,400
Evil down to the bone.

36
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:36,167
But why?

37
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,167
Son...

38
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:41,800
Why did they kidnap you?

39
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,600
Why did she do this to you?

40
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,767
You idiot!
Don't you think at all?

41
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,867
Why did you let Jeffrey go, huh?

42
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,333
We're going to prison.
Don't you get that?

43
00:02:02,467 --> 00:02:05,333
I can no longer stand
what you're doing!

44
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:06,933
Even to their family.

45
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:09,100
They're good people, Hazel.

46
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:14,133
Do you hear yourself?

47
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,233
They've brainwashed you!

48
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,667
No.

49
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,400
I'm not stupid enough
not to know the truth.

50
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:23,333
They loved Jessica
like family.

51
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:26,433
You're the one
who played the victim.

52
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,733
You lied.

53
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:31,167
You pretended they abused you.

54
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,733
But they're good people.

55
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:34,633
They're not evil.

56
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:35,933
So what now?

57
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:38,567
You're switching sides?

58
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,567
You're defending them?

59
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,433
Let me remind you.

60
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,633
They're not related to you.

61
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:46,533
Jessica is your blood.

62
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,300
- You're supposed to avenge her!
- Enough! Enough!

63
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,600
I'm done being fooled by you.

64
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:53,500
Let's stop this.

65
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:54,533
I don't want this anymore.

66
00:02:56,067 --> 00:02:57,933
That's not happening.

67
00:02:58,167 --> 00:03:00,067
I won't give up!

68
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:08,067
Hazel,

69
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:09,767
you must surrender now.

70
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:12,033
You animal!

71
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,967
You really brought
the cops here?

72
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,633
- Stop it! Stop it!
- You called them?

73
00:03:18,767 --> 00:03:20,333
Hazel!

74
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,567
Hazel!

75
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:23,033
Surrender...

76
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:52,500
Hazel was the mastermind
behind everything.

77
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,600
She couldn't accept

78
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,567
that Coleen was innocent
in what happened to Jessica.

79
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,733
So she took it out on us.

80
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:06,900
That stalker who kept
following you, Coleen...

81
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:08,733
Oh my God.

82
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:11,533
That witch is pure evil.

83
00:04:11,667 --> 00:04:13,533
And those guys who harassed you,
too.

84
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:17,733
She's so terrible.

85
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:20,733
I never thought
Hazel could do this.

86
00:04:20,867 --> 00:04:22,133
About...

87
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:24,300
about what happened to Joel...

88
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,433
was that her too?

89
00:04:27,633 --> 00:04:29,767
Why did Joel have
to get involved?

90
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,233
Because Joel found out about...

91
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,300
Hazel's connection to the man
she was talking to,

92
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:43,567
It was Jojo.

93
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,700
Jojo?

94
00:04:51,867 --> 00:04:53,733
Mom and Dad's therapist?

95
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:56,367
He's working with Hazel?

96
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,367
I thought he helped you escape.

97
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,067
Jeff, what really happened?

98
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,367
Son...

99
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,967
it's Tetay.

100
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,733
Dad, we're so happy
you got home safe.

101
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:22,233
Mom and I were so worried.

102
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:24,200
We couldn't even sleep.

103
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:29,933
We kept thinking
about our plans.

104
00:05:30,067 --> 00:05:32,467
Our family time together.

105
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:37,867
God didn't abandon you, Dad.

106
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,900
Thank you for your
prayers, sweetie.

107
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:45,567
Daisy, I really thought
I'd never see you again.

108
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:49,467
I had so many dreams for us.
I thought that was the end.

109
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,533
Jeff, we'll still see each
other.

110
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:54,967
We still have
a long time together.

111
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:58,600
Dad, do you want us
to come home?

112
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:01,667
We'll help you fight Hazel.

113
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,167
No need, sweetie.

114
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:06,800
Hazel won't hurt
anyone again.

115
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:11,633
We already reported her to the
police. She's going to jail.

116
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:14,500
Jeff, Jojo's here.

117
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:18,900
I'll call you back later.

118
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:20,533
Take care. Love you.

119
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:23,967
Okay, Dad. Bye. Be safe.
Love you.

120
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:36,700
Alice.

121
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:39,667
Alice.

122
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Help me.

123
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:44,400
Hide me.

124
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,767
Hide you?

125
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,067
From who?

126
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,800
Where? Hazel, I don't want
to be dragged into this.

127
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:52,000
You don't have a choice.
You're already involved.

128
00:06:53,233 --> 00:06:54,600
Alice!

129
00:06:56,467 --> 00:07:00,233
- Mrs. Cruz, surrender now!
- Sir, I'm not...

130
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:02,167
- Come with us. Get in.
- No, wait!

131
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,167
Wait!

132
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:03,833
- Hold on!
- Come on, move!

133
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:06,133
Wait! Alice!

134
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:09,600
Let go of me already!

135
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:11,867
Look! I'm cuffed!

136
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,533
You're gripping me
way too tight!

137
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,200
Hey, take this off.

138
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,567
Come on!

139
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,300
This isn't due process, okay?

140
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:22,700
You arrested me right away

141
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,100
just because someone filed
a complaint against me.

142
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:26,800
You don't even have a warrant!
Take this off!

143
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:29,800
Mrs. Cruz, the victim himself,
Jeffrey Cruz,

144
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,933
came here to file the complaint.

145
00:07:32,067 --> 00:07:33,167
He identified you

146
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,833
as the mastermind
behind his kidnapping.

147
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:38,600
Jojo Cañares backed it up.

148
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:42,967
So your arrest
is within protocol.

149
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,433
I didn't do anything wrong!

150
00:07:44,567 --> 00:07:47,733
Don't you know
"innocent until proven guilty"?

151
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:50,800
And I'll prove I'm innocent.

152
00:07:50,933 --> 00:07:53,900
Give me my phone.
I'm calling my lawyer now!

153
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:56,667
Give me your hand.
I'll take this off.

154
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,900
Finally.
Should've done that earlier.

155
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:00,400
Took you long enough.

156
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:05,233
That's as far as you can use
your phone, Ma'am.

157
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:06,700
Cellphones aren't allowed
in the cell.

158
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:08,867
Well, I'm not going to jail.

159
00:08:09,133 --> 00:08:12,767
My lawyer will do everything
to get me out on bail, okay?

160
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:14,600
What are you talking about?

161
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:17,467
What? What's so funny?

162
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,333
You know what?
You've been rough with me.

163
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:22,067
I could sue you
for police brutality!

164
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:25,100
Ma'am, you're the one who's
been violent since earlier.

165
00:08:25,233 --> 00:08:27,533
We could charge you
with assault.

166
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,467
Do you want to add another
case to your list?

167
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:36,667
Ma'am Felma, Sir Manuel...

168
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:39,400
I'm sorry for everything
that happened.

169
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:42,467
So...

170
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,200
You're admitting...

171
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:51,300
you conspired with Hazel?

172
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,333
- You bastard!
- Manuel!

173
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:59,567
- Dad!
- Manuel!

174
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:00,633
Dad, stop it!

175
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:02,667
We trusted you!

176
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:05,033
And this is how you repay us?

177
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,933
You even put my son in danger?

178
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:08,300
You animal!

179
00:09:11,433 --> 00:09:12,433
I'm sorry.

180
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:16,233
Hazel made me believe that...

181
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,200
you were bad people.

182
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,333
That you were the reason
our child died.

183
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,633
What child?

184
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:30,600
- Which child?
- Enough! Dad!

185
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,300
Who?

186
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,567
Jessica.

187
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,500
I'm her real father.

188
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:55,933
What?

189
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,367
You're resigning?

190
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:00,867
Attorney Salazar,
you can't do this.

191
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,267
I need you.

192
00:10:02,533 --> 00:10:04,767
You should already be here
posting my bail.

193
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:08,300
Attorney. Hello?

194
00:10:08,533 --> 00:10:09,800
Attorney Salazar?

195
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:12,100
Attorney?

196
00:10:12,233 --> 00:10:14,600
Ma'am, maybe you forgot.

197
00:10:14,733 --> 00:10:16,100
You're charged with kidnapping.

198
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:18,900
There's no bail for that.

199
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:21,300
You're going to rot in jail.

200
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:23,267
Attorney Salazar is good.

201
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,267
He can prove I'm innocent.

202
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,967
Just wait.
I'll have him come here.

203
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,833
What do you mean you're
Jessica's father?

204
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,067
Enough...

205
00:10:37,233 --> 00:10:38,733
How did that happen?

206
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,733
You're lying.

207
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:43,833
Both of you are liars.
You and Hazel!

208
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:45,667
Dad...

209
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,333
is Jessica's real father.

210
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:48,567
She's our sister.

211
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:51,700
Not you. Jessica is our sister.

212
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:57,000
I married Hazel because
she was pregnant with Jessica.

213
00:10:58,067 --> 00:10:59,367
Sir...

214
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,533
Hazel and I
were in a relationship.

215
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,433
I was also working
in Saudi Arabia at the time.

216
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,900
I was scared
to face my responsibility.

217
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:13,367
So I ran away.

218
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,400
<i>You got me pregnant.
You're the father.</i>

219
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:19,100
<i> That's impossible.</i>

220
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:21,300
<i> That's not my child.</i>

221
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:22,600
<i> What do you take me for?</i>

222
00:11:22,733 --> 00:11:24,500
<i> Someone who sleeps around?</i>

223
00:11:24,633 --> 00:11:25,767
<i> It only happened once!</i>

224
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:28,733
<i>It only takes once
for a woman to get pregnant.</i>

225
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:31,100
<i>But Hazel, that just happened...</i>

226
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,667
You bastard!

227
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:36,367
You dumped
your responsibility on me!

228
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:39,433
- Enough, Dad!
- Bastard!

229
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:44,067
You destroyed my life!

230
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:47,000
You destroyed my family
because of what you did!

231
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,700
I'm sorry, Sir.

232
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:54,733
- You bastard!
- Enough!

233
00:11:54,867 --> 00:11:56,500
- Sir!
- Dad!

234
00:11:56,633 --> 00:12:00,867
Son, I can never bring
back the time we lost.

235
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,367
And you?

236
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,633
Do you know
how my problems multiplied

237
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,133
because of what you did?

238
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:10,800
The woman I loved left me.

239
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:12,933
My eldest disowned me.

240
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:15,433
I forced myself
to stay with Hazel.

241
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,700
Then I ended up paralyzed.

242
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,300
So go on, tell me.

243
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:20,200
How am I supposed
to forgive you?

244
00:12:29,167 --> 00:12:33,433
And now you came back
and teamed up with that woman?

245
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:34,867
And hurt my family?

246
00:12:36,033 --> 00:12:38,167
You've got some nerve!

247
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,867
What did my kids ever do to you?

248
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,433
- What?
- Dad, stop it!

249
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:45,433
Dad, I get why you're angry.

250
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:48,733
I felt the same
when I heard the truth.

251
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,467
Dad, please listen to Jojo.

252
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:54,867
So you can understand.

253
00:13:01,233 --> 00:13:03,367
What was your real motive, Jojo?

254
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:06,733
If you're really her father,

255
00:13:06,867 --> 00:13:10,700
why did you work with Hazel?

256
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,567
What did we ever do to you?

257
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,367
She told me...

258
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,100
you were the reason
our child died.

259
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,067
That when you found out

260
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:31,533
Jessica wasn't really
your father's child,

261
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:35,400
you abused her...

262
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:36,700
<i> They mistreated Jessica.</i>

263
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:40,633
<i>They hurt her so badly
that she became depressed.</i>

264
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:43,100
<i> Until our child died.</i>

265
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,833
Those are lies.

266
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,367
That's not true.

267
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,400
We loved Jessica.

268
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:55,533
She wasn't depressed.

269
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:58,167
We never treated her that way.

270
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,267
The truth is,

271
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,567
we didn't even know she wasn't
really our sister.

272
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:06,467
Jojo...

273
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:10,400
Jessica's death was an accident.

274
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,533
<i>- Jessica, please!
- No!</i>

275
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,233
<i> Jessica!</i>

276
00:14:13,367 --> 00:14:15,267
<i> Jessica!</i>

277
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,233
<i> Jessica!</i>

278
00:14:20,133 --> 00:14:21,967
So Sir Manuel
was telling the truth.

279
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:24,900
Hazel was lying.

280
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:26,867
As Jessica grew up,

281
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,000
<i>I realized how wrong
my decision was.</i>

282
00:14:31,167 --> 00:14:33,233
<i> Manuel was cruel.</i>

283
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,700
<i> He already had another family.</i>

284
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:38,233
<i> They weren't married.</i>

285
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:42,100
<i>So that's why he had the nerve
to marry me.</i>

286
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:44,700
<i>He wanted my money
for his family.</i>

287
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:47,900
<i>To fund his family's business
here in the Philippines.</i>

288
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,600
That woman is a compulsive liar.

289
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:57,300
I never abused her,
especially not Jessica.

290
00:14:59,967 --> 00:15:05,200
Manuel didn't get
a single cent from her.

291
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:10,900
I raised our kids on my own.

292
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:18,633
We treated Jessica
like a real sister.

293
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:21,667
I'll admit, we fought sometimes.

294
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:25,000
But it never got to the point
that she became depressed.

295
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,067
I believe that.

296
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:32,100
I'm sorry...

297
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,333
it took me so long
to see the truth.

298
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:38,167
I let my anger get
the best of me.

299
00:15:40,267 --> 00:15:42,300
I blamed you
for her death.

300
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,233
I thought...

301
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:50,567
I'd find my family.

302
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:56,767
I thought I'd be with her again.

303
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:59,033
That I'd get to...

304
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:01,233
kiss her,

305
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,333
hold her.

306
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,500
But that will
never happen now.

307
00:16:09,567 --> 00:16:11,700
I'll never get the chance
to make it up to my daughter.

308
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,767
It hurts so much ...

309
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:21,000
knowing I was already too late.

310
00:16:22,567 --> 00:16:25,333
That's why Hazel
encouraged me to...

311
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:28,400
avenge Jessica.

312
00:16:29,633 --> 00:16:31,000
I grabbed the chance to...

313
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,833
become your therapist,
Ma'am Felma.

314
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:37,067
<i>How's Flirty Felma as a patient?</i>

315
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:39,133
<i> She's easy to win over.</i>

316
00:16:39,267 --> 00:16:42,533
<i>I think
she trusts me completely.</i>

317
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,033
<i> Very good.</i>

318
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:50,567
Just remember, you're doing all
this for our daughter Jessica.

319
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,567
Coleen...

320
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:00,400
I was your stalker.

321
00:17:01,533 --> 00:17:03,133
Hazel ordered me to do it.

322
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,233
<i>It feels like someone's
following me.</i>

323
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:06,533
<i> Coleen, run!</i>

324
00:17:06,667 --> 00:17:08,100
<i> Help!</i>

325
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:09,533
<i> Somebody help me!</i>

326
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:12,067
Andrea...

327
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:15,500
the guys who harassed you...

328
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:18,600
were Hazel's men.

329
00:17:19,533 --> 00:17:21,000
<i> Hi, Miss Beautiful.</i>

330
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:22,633
<i> Come with us.</i>

331
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:23,633
<i> Hey, stay away.</i>

332
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:25,467
<i> Come on. Let's go.</i>

333
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,900
<i>- Let's go!
- You're disgusting!</i>

334
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:33,333
Did Hazel kill Joel?

335
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:39,200
And you helped her do it?

336
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:52,933
<i>They were saying at
the hospital that he overdosed.</i>

337
00:17:53,067 --> 00:17:54,200
<i> You killed him?</i>

338
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:57,367
<i>All I wanted was to make
it look like he was on drugs.</i>

339
00:17:57,500 --> 00:18:01,467
<i>So if he talked to Felma, they'd
think he was hallucinating.</i>

340
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:05,000
<i>I didn't know
his body was that weak.</i>

341
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,367
Why did you do that?

342
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:20,733
Joel had nothing
to do with this.

343
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,967
You didn't have to kill him.

344
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:27,167
You didn't have to go that far.

345
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:30,033
I never thought it would
end like this, Andrea.

346
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:36,333
Hazel made me believe
everything we were doing...

347
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:38,167
was for Jessica.

348
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:42,300
But when I saw all of you...

349
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,067
you're good people.

350
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:50,467
I could feel that
you truly loved my daughter.

351
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,133
That's when I knew it was wrong.

352
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,500
I couldn't take it anymore.

353
00:18:58,233 --> 00:19:00,367
I helped Jeffrey escape.

354
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:03,567
I hope...

355
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:06,733
I hope you can forgive me.

356
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,567
The truth is, I hate myself.

357
00:19:11,967 --> 00:19:15,100
Because I'm the reason
I never got to see my daughter.

358
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:16,900
Because I left her.

359
00:19:18,967 --> 00:19:20,700
And now I'll never be with her.

360
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:24,467
Please forgive me.

361
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:37,800
Alice, pick up.

362
00:19:38,067 --> 00:19:38,833
- Alice.
- Ma'am,

363
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:40,000
you've been on the phone
for a while now.

364
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,000
Wait, just a second.

365
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:44,900
My friend isn't answering.
One moment.

366
00:19:45,033 --> 00:19:46,300
So what now, Ma'am?

367
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:53,433
Darn it.

368
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:56,900
Ma'am, it looks like
you don't have a lawyer anymore.

369
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:07,133
My friend won't answer.

370
00:20:07,267 --> 00:20:09,933
Ma'am, if you can't reach
a lawyer,

371
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:12,200
we can request one from the
Public Attorney's Office.

372
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,600
PAO?

373
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:17,900
Those are the pro
bono lawyers, right?

374
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,467
Are they even good?

375
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,233
What if they don't try hard
since they're not getting paid?

376
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:25,033
Mrs. Cruz,
don't underestimate them.

377
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,433
They're very capable.

378
00:20:27,567 --> 00:20:29,767
And besides,
do you even have a choice?

379
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:37,100
For years, I forced myself
to get along with Hazel

380
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:38,733
for Jessica's sake.

381
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,900
Then I found out
she wasn't really my daughter.

382
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,200
You know...

383
00:20:46,233 --> 00:20:48,400
that child was the real victim.

384
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,233
She grew up living
in her mother's lies.

385
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,767
She wasn't our blood,

386
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:02,433
but she loved and accepted us as
her siblings with all her heart.

387
00:21:04,267 --> 00:21:06,933
Do you think she knew
the truth before she died?

388
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,800
Whether she knew or not,

389
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,533
it doesn't change anything.

390
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,967
Because she still loved
all of us.

391
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:21,500
And we loved her too...

392
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:22,933
with everything we had.

393
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,067
Even if it was only for a
while...

394
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:30,033
she was our family.

395
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,100
She was our youngest.

396
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,600
And that's how
it should be.

397
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:42,800
No matter what happened,

398
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:47,900
we'll always love Jessica...

399
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:50,067
as family.

400
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,433
Thank you so
much, Ma'am Felma.

401
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,500
Jeffrey.

402
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,133
Andrea.

403
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:08,600
Coleen.

404
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,267
Didang.

405
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:14,833
Sir Manuel.

406
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:18,033
Honestly?

407
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:21,567
I envy you.

408
00:22:21,933 --> 00:22:22,967
Because...

409
00:22:25,033 --> 00:22:27,867
you experienced
how Jessica loved.

410
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:34,633
You had the chance to love her.

411
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:37,633
To hold her.

412
00:22:38,933 --> 00:22:40,567
Kiss her.

413
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,200
You had...

414
00:22:43,333 --> 00:22:45,567
so many chances...

415
00:22:45,833 --> 00:22:47,333
to be a father to her.

416
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:49,667
Me?

417
00:22:51,067 --> 00:22:52,733
That will never happen.

418
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:00,433
You did that in your own way.

419
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:03,933
You became a father
when you chose to help Jeffrey.

420
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:06,700
We'll always be grateful
to you for that, Jojo.

421
00:23:09,133 --> 00:23:11,567
If you hadn't saved Jeffrey,

422
00:23:13,967 --> 00:23:16,000
who knows
what would've happened to him.

423
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,467
Thank you. Thank you so much.

424
00:23:50,967 --> 00:23:52,133
Cruz, you have a visitor.

425
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:53,567
You're a devil, Hazel!

426
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,867
Jessica wasn't even
really my daughter!

427
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:58,767
Is it my fault you're stupid?

428
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,233
You're unbelievable.

429
00:24:00,367 --> 00:24:03,000
You used Manuel, and you still
have the nerve to insult him.

430
00:24:04,267 --> 00:24:06,367
You shameless woman!

431
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,433
Aren't you scared?

432
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:10,533
You were involved
in Joel Santiago's death.

433
00:24:10,667 --> 00:24:13,233
I only committed one sin
against you, Manuel,

434
00:24:13,367 --> 00:24:15,567
but you destroyed
my entire life.

435
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:16,867
I won't let this end here.

436
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,433
I still have a card left to
play.
